QUESTION NO: 1
When creating a Build Forge Project, what is a required attribute of a Project?
A. Manifest
B. Collector
C. Selector
D. Notification
Answer: D
QUESTION NO: 2
What is a primary differentiator between Build Forge and competing products where
Build Forge provides significant business value?
A. It treats the build process as a complete end-to-end process.
B. It provides enhanced editors and debuggers for the development process.
C. It eliminates the unit testing that would normally be required.
D. It optimizes much of the source code before each build run.
Answer: A
QUESTION NO: 3
When manually executing a Build Forge Project, the Job Details tab in the Management
Console allows you to view and change some of the Project's default parameters. Which
parameter can be changed under the Job Details tab?
A. Selector
B. Access
C. Pass/Fail Chain
D. Max Threads
Answer: A
